  "prompt": "What are some TL;DRs of each of the most important governors of California?",
  "response": "Here are some TLDRs (Too Long; Didn\u2019t Read) summaries of some of California's most significant governors:\n\n1. **Jerry Brown (1975\u20131983, 2011\u20132019)**  \n   Known as \"Governor Moonbeam\" for his unconventional ideas, he championed environmental policies, fiscal restraint, and renewable energy. His second term focused on climate change, criminal justice reform, and balancing the budget.\n\n2. **Arnold Schwarzenegger (2003\u20132011)**  \n   The \"Governator\" brought star power to politics, focusing on climate change (AB 32), infrastructure, and bipartisan (sometimes contentious) governance. He famously battled with unions and had mixed success in reforming California\u2019s budget.\n\n3. **Ronald Reagan (1967\u20131975)**  \n   A rising conservative star, Reagan cut taxes, cracked down on student protests, and streamlined government. His tenure set the stage for his presidency and the national conservative movement.\n\n4. **Earl Warren (1943\u20131953)**  \n   A progressive Republican, Warren modernized California\u2019s infrastructure, education, and healthcare. Later, as Chief Justice of the U.S. Supreme Court, he led landmark civil rights decisions.\n\n5. **Pete Wilson (1991\u20131999)**  \n   A controversial figure, Wilson aggressively tackled illegal immigration (Prop 187) and economic issues, but his policies alienated many Latino voters and fueled political polarization.\n\n6. **Gray Davis (1999\u20132003)**  \n   Davis faced the dot-com bust and energy crisis (Enron scandal), leading to a recall election. He was ousted, becoming the second U.S. governor ever to be recalled.\n\n7. **Edmund G. \"Pat\" Brown (1959\u20131967)**  \n   Oversaw California\u2019s mid-20th-century boom, expanding water infrastructure (California State Water Project), higher education (UC system), and highways. Known as a visionary builder.\n\n8. **Gavin Newsom (2019\u2013present)**  \n   A progressive leader, Newsom has focused on climate action, COVID-19 response, healthcare expansion, and addressing homelessness. His tenure has been marked by bold policies and controversies.\n\nEach governor shaped California\u2019s trajectory in unique ways, reflecting the state\u2019s evolving political and social landscape.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
